						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone built into the tank-bund near the village.</p>						

						<p>Jayakēśi II.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription is dated in the 13th year of the reign of Kadamba Jayakēśi Siddhārthi, Bhādrapada ba. 5, Sunday. Irregular.</p>						

						<p>It states that Kāmaya-daṇṇāyaka and refers to the capture of cattle by Habbeya-Nāyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
